<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") -%>
<h1 class="text-center mt-2">Project Details</h1>
<div class="card mb-3 bg-transparent mt-3 mb-5">
  <img src="/images/Calculator.png" class="card-img-top rounded shadow w-75 mx-auto" alt="img">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title text-center"><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Calculator (HTML, CSS & JavaScript)</h5>
    <p class="card-text text-center">“A Simple Yet Powerful Tool for Everyday Calculations!”</p>
    <p class="card-text text-center">
      This project is a fully functional calculator built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, capable of performing basic arithmetic operations. It focuses on core DOM manipulation and event handling, making it a great exercise in connecting user input with dynamic logic.
    </p>
    <p><b>Key Features:</b>
    <ul>
      <li><i class="fas fa-plus"></i> Arithmetic Operations: Addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
      </li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-mouse-pointer"></i> Interactive Buttons: User-friendly interface with clickable number and operator buttons.
      </li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-sync-alt"></i> Clear & Reset: AC (All Clear) and delete functionality for error handling.
      </li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i> Responsive Layout: Styled with CSS to adapt to different devices.</li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-code"></i> Core Logic: Written entirely in vanilla JavaScript, without external libraries.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p><b>What I Learned:</b></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Attaching event listeners to multiple elements.</li>
        <li>Managing application state (current input, previous input, operator).</li>
        <li>Updating the DOM dynamically based on user actions.</li>
        <li>Writing clean, modular JavaScript functions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>-> This project highlights my ability to combine interactivity with functionality, turning a simple idea into a practical and visually engaging web tool.</p>
    <p style="color: gray">
        <span style="color: red;">DISCLAIMER</span>: In This Project The Style Part Is Inspired By ChatGpt But The JavaScript Part Is Written By Me.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>